			<p>Not an impressive proportion, to be sure. Is it easy to tell what proportion of their <i>articles are in the OA journals? For example, I don&#8217;t know whether </i><i>SAGE Open</i> is unusually voluminous.</p>
<p>In saying that SAGE is pushing towards OA, I was thinking more of stuff like <a href="http://blog.peerj.com/post/91251985913/exciting-times-peerj-secures-next-round-of-funding-led" rel="nofollow">We are delighted to partner with a publisher that has been such an early advocate for open access publishing. For example, SAGE formed a partnership with Hindawi Publishing Corporation in 2007, and was also a founding board member of OASPA in 2008.</a></p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_230587_comm_142221"></div>
