			<p>Yes. Your point is well made and well taken. There is certainly something comforting about PLOS&#8217;s well-defined mission, and in one sense it&#8217;s a shame that PeerJ lacks that. On the other hand, it&#8217;s probably good for the diversity of the dedicated-OA publishing ecosystem that it&#8217;s inhabited by both non-profits and for-profits.</p>
