	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dwojick even depth-6 highlander-comment" id="li-comment-142235">

		<div class="commentcont" id="comment-142235">

							<div class="fright"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0e1c95b04d4d8dde488f86059c0d8be1?s=40&#038;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D40' class='avatar avatar-40' height='40' width='40' /></div>
			
			<p>David C, any idea what percentage of OUP articles is OA, as opposed to journals? I would not be surprised to see 10% as the ultimate OA market segment, but this is not a prediction, far from it.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_230587_comm_142235"></div>
			<p>
							</p>

			<cite>
				Posted by <span class="commentauthor">David Wojick</span> | <a href="#comment-142235" title="">Jul 24, 2014, 11:32 am</a> 			</cite>

		</div>

